<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Keckiella</i> <i>antirrhinoides</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Adenostoma</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Artemisia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Cneoridium</i> <i>dumosum</i>, <i>Eriodictyon</i> <i>crassifolium</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Hesperoyucca</i> <i>whipplei</i>, <i>Malosma</i> <i>laurina</i>, <i>Quercus</i> <i>berberidifolia</i>, <i>Rhus</i> <i>ovata</i>, <i>Salvia</i> <i>apiana</i>, <i>Salvia</i> <i>mellifera</i>, <i>Tetradymia</i> <i>comosa</i> and <i>Xylococcus</i> <i>bicolor</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Quercus</i> <i>engelmannii</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 2 m; canopy is open to continuous and two tiered. Herbaceous layer is open to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Keckiella antirrhinoides</i> > 30% in the shrub canopy as a dominant or co-dominant with other shrubs (Evens and San 2005, Klein and Evens 2005).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Variable topography, though well developed on north-facing hillsides. Soils are loams and clays derived from granitic or gabbro substrates.  </div>
</div>

        
